    "A story also has an internal speed that governs the ex-Fig. 1: Preparation Architecture ercise's overall pace with an optional descriptionfoot_0.",
    "Scripts: Scripts are the sub-stories that dictate the timeline of a cybersecurity exercise, with a start and end time expressed in seconds, and a speed indicating how quickly the script progresses.",
    "Events within the script are scheduled to start at precise times, such as 'event-1' at the outset and 'event-2' five minutes later. 3.",
    "Events: Events serve as sets of rules that outline specific conditions.",
    "When these conditions become valid, the associated injects within that event are activated."
